# Legacy — the user's persistent memory agent

The user has a memory agent whose knowledge graph (Cognee) persists across
every chat and every tool. This session is amnesiac; Legacy is not.

Run via terminal (works from any directory):

- Recall:   `~/hangover/legacy ask "<question about the user's work, projects, goals>"`
- Capture:  `~/hangover/legacy remember "<one dense sentence about what they did/decided>"`
- Evidence: `~/hangover/legacy observe`   (run inside the project's git repo)
- Deep-learn a finished project (metadata only): `~/hangover/legacy learn`
- Session end (user taught you commands/rituals): `echo "<summary>" | ~/hangover/legacy distill -`

When the user says "build it like <past project>" or "combine my apps X and Y":
first run `legacy ask` to get each project's stack, architecture, features and
patterns, then design from that answer. When they finish substantial work:
`remember` it, and `observe` + `learn` from the project directory.

Adjust `~/hangover` to wherever the Legacy repo is cloned.
